* Grouped Alphabetical Listing
* Organizes Participants into Visual Sections
* When to use:      Use this when you want a report separated by headers - for example, grouping everyone from the same Club, State, or shared Last Name together.
* How to use:       The BY command creates a new section header every time the data in that field changes. Pair it with SORT to alphabetize the individuals within those specific groups.


* Note: use an empty comparand after <> - a literal "" matches two quote
*       characters, not an empty string, and would exclude nothing.
Select              LAST NAME
<>
By                  LAST NAME
Sort                FIRST NAME
Destination         Browser
 